This version of Ariana Grande’s song “No Tears Left to Cry” sounds a bit cardboardy. But that’s a good thing. Because on Monday’s broadcast of “The Tonight Show,” Grande joined host Jimmy Fallon and house band The Roots to perform her latest single using new Nintendo Switch accessory Labo and instruments predominantly made from the paper product.  “It was totally bizarre and such a gamble,” Fallon told IGN. “I didn’t know if it was going to sound good, but Ariana is always down to try something fun and different.” Check out the clip above and see how it compares to the original below: